TY  - JOUR
AU  - Valmari, Nelli
T1  - Estimating Production Functions of Multiproduct Firms
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdad005
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 90
IS  - 6
SP  - 3315
EP  - 3342
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Multiproduct firms constitute a considerable share of firms and account for an even greater share of production. Nevertheless, the vast majority of production function estimates are based on the assumption that firms are single-product manufacturers. This assumption is due to a lack of data on how firms allocate their inputs across their various product lines. I provide a strategy for estimating product-specific input allocations and production functions of multiproduct firms involved in monopolistic competition. The strategy is based on using firms’ product prices and output demand in solving for product-level input allocations.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdad005
ER  - 



