TY  - JOUR
AU  - Andrews, Isaiah
AU  - Roth, Jonathan
AU  - Pakes, Ariel
T1  - Inference for Linear Conditional Moment Inequalities
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdad004
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 90
IS  - 6
SP  - 2763
EP  - 2791
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We show that moment inequalities in a wide variety of economic applications have a particular linear conditional structure. We use this structure to construct uniformly valid confidence sets that remain computationally tractable even in settings with nuisance parameters. We first introduce least-favorable critical values which deliver non-conservative tests if all moments are binding. Next, we introduce a novel conditional inference approach which ensures a strong form of insensitivity to slack moments. Our recommended approach is a hybrid technique which combines desirable aspects of the least favorable and conditional methods. The hybrid approach performs well in simulations calibrated to Wollmann (2018, American Economic Review, 108, 1364–1406), with favorable power and computational time comparisons relative to existing alternatives.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdad004
ER  - 



